Zercher squats are satisfying because they lead to completion. With regular squats you can go down and down deep into the grass without stimulus, but with Zerchers you feel your elbows pressing against knees and thighs. It's like a little bell ringing to mark the rep. Completion.

"Thot" was black people's awkward linguistic attempt at preemptively reaching the elegance of the word "foid". Like a linguistic St.-John-who-weeps summer solstice that must recede to make way for winter. When you type "foid" in StarCraft Korean-to-English it comes out as "thot".

As "lol" (actually a 16th century Dutch word for joyous feelings and felicity) stands to "kek", thus "foid" is also to "thot". "Foid" is a word of gentle love expressing care for women and comes from the Adamic language of the birds (which coincidentally also happens to be Dutch)

There is a very particular feeling you sense only when you climb a mountain, either when you look back during the climb or when you reach the peak, that can only be described as a sort of "lesser omniscience", all-seeingness. You are aware of the increase of your sight's capacity

You read stories of saints or people in states close to death leaving their body and going towards Heaven and they describe rising above the city and "being able to see everything", including inside the rooms of apartments, etc. The bird's eye view being a dominant characteristic

Gene Wolfe also mentions this in BoTNS at the peak of Typhon the old Autarch in the mountains, where Severian was able to see everything in the world like from a vantage point. Omniscience is very much related to vertical superiority in space. From above you feel you can see all.

Really "naming" people, living things, objects, etc. seems to be the essence of Demiurgery, all things find their first cause in God, but naming makes one sub-creator. Or in Tolkien's naming, Eru telling Melkor that the music he adds to His creation also finds its source in Him.
Salvation is simply objectivity reasserting itself over subjectivity.
